<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="117" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="117">
<taxonomicName LSID="http://zoobank.org/6A3DCAC3-1857-4AA6-8A72-0F0C20D4B50F" authority=")" authorityName="Roza &amp; Schrago &amp; Mermudes" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Cicindelidae" genus="Mesochila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Mesochila (Neomesochila)" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" status="subgen. nov." subGenus="Neomesochila">Mesochila (Neomesochila)</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="0" pageNumber="117">subgen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="117" type="type species">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Type species.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="117">
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Odontocheila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Odontocheila brevipennis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevipennis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Odontocheila brevipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
W. Horn, 1907
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="117" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="117">
Composed word formed by 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">neo</emphasis>
(from Greek, means new) and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rivalier" authorityYear="1969" class="Insecta" family="Cicindelidae" genus="Mesochila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Mesochila" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Mesochila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the genus name.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="117" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Smaller body length, usually between 6-9.3 mm; mandibles with four teeth (plus molar one); pronotum as wide as long; elytra 3.3-3.6 times longer than wide, finely punctate; aedeagus thin, with apical third subparallel, with apex forming distinctly wide bent rounded beak, internal sac containing stingray-like ventral spur and an oval feebly sclerotized central sclerite.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="117">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">4 species included</emphasis>
:
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="117">
路 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. (N.) brevipennis" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" rank="species" species="brevipennis" subGenus="N.">M. (N.) brevipennis</taxonomicName>
(W. Horn, 1907)
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="117">
路 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. (N.) drechseli" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" rank="species" species="drechseli" subGenus="N.">M. (N.) drechseli</taxonomicName>
(Sawada and Wiesner, 1997)
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="117">
路 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. (N.) moraveci" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" rank="species" species="moraveci" subGenus="N.">M. (N.) moraveci</taxonomicName>
(Roza and Mermudes, 2019)
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="117">
路 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. (N.) prepusula" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" rank="species" species="prepusula" subGenus="N.">M. (N.) prepusula</taxonomicName>
(W. Horn, 1907)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="117" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="117">
It is interesting to point out that the stingray-like ventral spur (term proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Moravec, J" journalOrPublisher="Acta Musei Moraviae, Scientiae Biologicae (Brno)" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" pagination="127 - 206" refId="B30" refString="Moravec, J, 2018a. Taxonomic and nomenclatorial revision within the Neotropical genera of the subtribe Odontocheilina W. Horn in a new sense - 20. Beckerium W. Horn stat. restit., Mesochila Rivalier stat. nov. and Poecilochila Rivalier stat. nov. Acta Musei Moraviae, Scientiae Biologicae (Brno) 103 (2): 127 - 206" title="Taxonomic and nomenclatorial revision within the Neotropical genera of the subtribe Odontocheilina W. Horn in a new sense - 20. Beckerium W. Horn stat. restit., Mesochila Rivalier stat. nov. and Poecilochila Rivalier stat. nov." volume="103" year="2018 a">Moravec 2018a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Moravec, J." journalOrPublisher="Biosfericka rezervace Dolni Morava: Lednice na Morave, Czech Republic" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" refId="B32" refString="Moravec, J., 2020. . Taxonomic revision of the Neotropical tiger beetle genera of the subtribe Odontocheilina - Volume 2. A complete revision of other twelve genera of the subtribe (Coleoptera: Cicindelidae). Biosfericka rezervace Dolni Morava: Lednice na Morave, Czech Republic" title=". Taxonomic revision of the Neotropical tiger beetle genera of the subtribe Odontocheilina - Volume 2. A complete revision of other twelve genera of the subtribe (Coleoptera: Cicindelidae)." year="2020">2020</bibRefCitation>
), one of the most distinct features of 
<taxonomicName authority="" genus="M." lsidName="M. (Mesochila)" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Mesochila">M. (Mesochila)</taxonomicName>
, present in almost all species previous to this study, was found to be homoplastic, with independent origins in 
<taxonomicName authority="" genus="M." lsidName="M. (Neomesochila)" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Neomesochila">M. (Neomesochila)</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">subgen. nov.</emphasis>
and inside 
<taxonomicName authority="" genus="M." lsidName="M. (Mesochila)" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Mesochila">M. (Mesochila)</taxonomicName>
, derived from bifurcate or u-shaped ventral spurs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="117">
Finally, it is important to highlight that the outgroup relationships suggest, in most analysis, a relationship between 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Dejean" baseAuthorityYear="1825" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Odontocheila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Odontocheila nodicornis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nodicornis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Odontocheila nodicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Phyllodroma" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Phyllodroma luteomaculata" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luteomaculata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Phyllodroma luteomaculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and in many of them, also between 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Brulle" baseAuthorityYear="1837" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pentacomia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pentacomia speculifera" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="speculifera">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Pentacomia speculifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="Mesachantina" lsidName="Mesachantina chalceola" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" rank="species" species="chalceola">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Mesachantina chalceola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. As already pointed out by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4127.2.3" author="Moravec, J" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" pagination="276 - 300" refId="B29" refString="Moravec, J, 2016. Taxonomic and nomenclatorial revision within the Neotropical genera of the subtribe Odontocheilina W. Horn in a new sense - 16. Pentacomia (Mesochila) procera (Chaudoir), P. (M.) conformis (Dejean), and P. (M.) proceroides sp. nov. (Coleoptera: Cicindelidae). Zootaxa 4127 (2): 276 - 300, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4127.2.3" title="Taxonomic and nomenclatorial revision within the Neotropical genera of the subtribe Odontocheilina W. Horn in a new sense - 16. Pentacomia (Mesochila) procera (Chaudoir), P. (M.) conformis (Dejean), and P. (M.) proceroides sp. nov. (Coleoptera: Cicindelidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4127.2.3" volume="4127" year="2016">Moravec (2016</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Moravec, J" journalOrPublisher="Acta Musei Moraviae, Scientiae Biologicae (Brno)" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" pagination="127 - 206" refId="B30" refString="Moravec, J, 2018a. Taxonomic and nomenclatorial revision within the Neotropical genera of the subtribe Odontocheilina W. Horn in a new sense - 20. Beckerium W. Horn stat. restit., Mesochila Rivalier stat. nov. and Poecilochila Rivalier stat. nov. Acta Musei Moraviae, Scientiae Biologicae (Brno) 103 (2): 127 - 206" title="Taxonomic and nomenclatorial revision within the Neotropical genera of the subtribe Odontocheilina W. Horn in a new sense - 20. Beckerium W. Horn stat. restit., Mesochila Rivalier stat. nov. and Poecilochila Rivalier stat. nov." volume="103" year="2018 a">2018a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Moravec, J" journalOrPublisher="Biosfericka rezervace Dolni Morava: Lednice na Morave, Czech Republic" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" refId="B31" refString="Moravec, J, 2018b. Taxonomic revision of the Neotropical tiger beetle genera of the subtribe Odontocheilina - Volume 1. Odontocheila Laporte de Castelnau, Cenothyla Rivalier and Phyllodroma Lacordaire (Coleoptera: Cicindelidae). Biosfericka rezervace Dolni Morava: Lednice na Morave, Czech Republic" title="Taxonomic revision of the Neotropical tiger beetle genera of the subtribe Odontocheilina - Volume 1. Odontocheila Laporte de Castelnau, Cenothyla Rivalier and Phyllodroma Lacordaire (Coleoptera: Cicindelidae)." year="2018 b">b</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Moravec, J." journalOrPublisher="Biosfericka rezervace Dolni Morava: Lednice na Morave, Czech Republic" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" refId="B32" refString="Moravec, J., 2020. . Taxonomic revision of the Neotropical tiger beetle genera of the subtribe Odontocheilina - Volume 2. A complete revision of other twelve genera of the subtribe (Coleoptera: Cicindelidae). Biosfericka rezervace Dolni Morava: Lednice na Morave, Czech Republic" title=". Taxonomic revision of the Neotropical tiger beetle genera of the subtribe Odontocheilina - Volume 2. A complete revision of other twelve genera of the subtribe (Coleoptera: Cicindelidae)." year="2020">2020</bibRefCitation>
), the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bates.The" authorityYear="1872" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pentacomia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pentacomia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Pentacomia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
former subgenera are probably not phylogenetically related, due to several morphological differences. The most conspicuous one is the uniformly shaped protarsi in both sexes in all 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bates.The" authorityYear="1872" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pentacomia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pentacomia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Pentacomia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species (unique character in the subtribe and within majority of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Cicindelidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Cicindelidae</taxonomicName>
). The same goes for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Laporte de Castelnau" authorityYear="1834" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Odontocheila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Odontocheila" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Odontocheila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lacordaire" authorityYear="1843" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Phyllodroma" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Phyllodroma" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Phyllodroma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, that share an aedeagus flagellum, but with very different morphology and most probably homoplastic (Moravec, 2018b). Only a broader analysis, including representative taxa from all 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lacordaire" authorityYear="1843" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Phyllodroma" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Odontocheilina">Odontocheilina</taxonomicName>
genera may give better understanding of the group relationships.
</paragraph>
